<br>
inner has no where to go, if they are a high dps group it is indeed possible to clear the entire cave.. most groups do not however thus the ability for inner + outter to coexist.  typically outer needs to be a low dps group duos etc or subsist off scraps from the cave and frogs + undead.. if you can't you need to move on.<br>
<br>
inner simply has no options otherwise.  <br>
<br>
if however inner is pulling the mobs nearest the outside of the cave (while leaving nearer mobs up in thier cave) just to screw over the outter group.. then of course thats lame.<br>
<br>
<br>
Converse is kinda true if you are an inner group and really really slow you shouldn't complain about an outter group snagging mobs from the inside.  I do this, but only if there is more than one mob up inside, 'straggling' xp groups really isnt cool, inner/outer has the highest incidence of this due to its setup, but just use a little consideration and realize that inner is in the back of a cave.. no where to go and it'll help alot with xp group relations. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><br>
